.SH "NAME"
umad_size \- get the size of umad buffer
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.nf
.B #include <infiniband/umad.h>
.sp
.BI "size_t umad_size(void);
.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.B umad_size()
returns the size of umad buffer (in bytes).
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.B umad_size()
returns the size of umad buffer (in bytes).
